FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE - TUNISIA: (NABEUL) SEROTYPE PENDING, BOVINE, OIE
**********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 29 Apr 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2014; 27(18) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15183


Foot-and-mouth disease, Tunisia
-------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 29 Apr 2014 from Dr Hichem Bouzghaia, [Director General, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture], Tunis, Tunisia.

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 25 Apr 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 26 Apr 2014
Report date: 29 Apr 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: March 1999
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Somaa, beni Khiar, Nabeul
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 17 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 2
Affected population: sick animals showed signs suggestive of foot-and-mouth disease (sores, ulcers, salivation)
Outbreak statistics (rates apparent, expressed as percentages)
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 11.76 / 0 / 0 / 11.76
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals
Epidemiological comments: on 20 Apr 2014, 2 animals, whose immune status was not known, were introduced into the farm. In addition to the control measures mentioned, the following measures are being implemented: - [activation] of crisis cells [or command centers] at national and regional levels; - burying of [offal] and bones between 2 layers of lime; - disinfection of vehicles leaving the affected governorates; - vaccination points of susceptible species at the entrance of livestock markets; - epidemiological investigation to determine the origin of the infection; - activation of a communication plan.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s) [see comment]; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); modified stamping out; no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Tunisian Veterinary Research Institute (IRVT) (national laboratory) / Cattle / real-time PCR / 26 Apr 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above. - Mod.CRD]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the immediate notification, vaccination is said to have been applied in response to the outbreak. The exact vaccine strain to be applied depends on the results of the serotyping, expected soonest. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2439461,32368.]
